%------------------------------- CONLCUS
{
\setbeamercolor{title}{fg=blue}
\setbeamercolor{normal text}{fg=black}
\setbeamercolor{frametitle}{fg=blue}
\usebeamercolor[fg]{normal text}
\usebackgroundtemplate{{\includegraphics[width=\paperwidth]
{figuras/fondo_poster_70x90cm.pdf}}}
\frame{ 
\titulo{EUV-SRT conclusions during deep minima}
\footnotesize

\btr General characteristics:\\
\bu Streamers exhibit $N_{CB} \approx 1.0-1.2\times 10^8\,{\rm cm}^{-3}$, CHs are characterized by half of that density. \\
\vskip 0.2cm
\bu $\lambda_N \approx 7-11\times 10^{-2}\,\mrsun$, the lower values corresponding to the lower latitudes of the streamer and CHs. \\
\vskip 0.2cm
\bu Streamers are characterized by $\left<T_m\right>\approx 1.2-1.6$~MK (the lowest temperatures corresponding to lower latitudes) while CHs exhibit $\left<T_m\right> \lesssim 1$~MK.\\
\vskip 0.2cm
\bu Loops with $\dTm_dr<0$ systematically found in the Streamer core of all minima $\rightarrow$ reproduced by Alfvén wave heating models (Schiff \& Cranmer, 2016) $\rightarrow$  Presents conditioning to the coronal heating model.
%\bu We found the presence of loops down in the 3 minima. Nuevo et al. (2013); Schiff and Cranmer (2016). Presents conditioning to the coronal heating model.\\
%Correlación entre número de líneas tipo 0 y mínimo de actividad.\\
%$\beta > 1$ favorece la conversión de ondas de Alfvén en modos compresibles.\\

\vskip 0.7cm
\btr Comparison of the last 3 minimums:\\
\bu $\left<T_m^{SC \, 22/23}\right>  > \left<T_m^{SC \, 23/24}\right>  \lesssim \left<T_m^{SC \, 24/25}\right> $\\
\vskip 0.2cm
\bu $N_{CB}^{SC \, 22/23} > N_{CB}^{SC \, 23/24} > N_{CB}^{SC \, 24/25}$\\
\vskip 0.2cm
\bu The global thermodynamic state of minima is not correlated with the activity level of a full cycle.
%\bu SC 22/23 fue el mas breve, activo e intermitente en su nivel de actividad, seguido por SC 23/24 y SC 24/25.\\
%\vskip 0.1cm
%\bu \# Loops down máximo durante SC 23/24.
}
}


